description:
&lt;h2&gt;Renal Information and Systems Manager&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full-time Information and Systems Manager at the Wessex Kidney Centre, based at Queen Alexandra hospital (Portsmouth Hospitals University Trust) in Portsmouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a busy and interesting role which is an important part of a large, regional renal treatment service. The post holder will be responsible for, among other responsibilities, maintaining an Electronic Patient Record system holding treatment information on approximately 12,000 active patients and used by hundreds of users across multiple sites. You will lead on data quality, reporting and overall system management including creating new users and answering user queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will frequently be tasked with carrying out complex analysis tasks to identify trends, support business cases, and inform audits. You will have a working understanding of MySQL databases and will be required to write SQL queries. You will need to be able to draw conclusions based on your analysis of treatment data and present your findings to various audiences ranging from senior management team members to Consultants and other clinicians. You will also oversee data submissions to bodies such as the UK Renal Registry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have significant experience in clinical informatics and analytics and will be used to working closely with colleagues at all levels, presenting information at an appropriate and tailored level depending on the audience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The WKC is constantly improving and developing. The holder of this post will be an integral part of project boards, providing analysis and informatics support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will of course be very familiar with software used in business settings, including the entire Microsoft Office suite and particularly MS Excel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like it might be the role for you, we wouldencourage you to apply. Informal telephone discussions are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 17/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
